The TV licence fee is guaranteed until 2027 when the broadcaster's charter is up for renewal. But in a mid-term review, Ms Dorries issued a legal direction including the target for 25 per cent of staff to be from low socio-economic backgrounds. She said it would "build on our recent progress to make the BBC more accountable to those who fund it."  She called on the corporation to "level up access to job opportunities".The broadcaster's commercial subsidiaries, including BBC Studios, will also face scrutiny so they do not create an unfair competitive advantage.